      <strong>Bookings</strong><br>
      <br>
      18. A player who receives a red card will be given an automatic one match 
      ban (ie he will miss the next League or Cup game).His photo would also be 
      appearing the Red Carded list on the web site. The respective team would 
      be fined $10/- for his action (which would be accumurted till end season 
      for Charity Fund. 
      <p>19 . A yellow card will earn the player and his Team one disciplinary 
        point on the disciplinary table which would add up for point deduction 
        range on Result Table after every 15 games. If the team collected 3 yellow 
        card on the same game, the team would be fined $10 as well.</p>
      <p>20 . A red card will earn the player and his Team three disciplinary 
        points on the disciplinary table which would add up for point deduction 
        range on Result Table after every 15 games.</p>
      <p>21 . Each week the League will publish tables showing the total disciplinary 
        points earned by each Team and each player. This would serve as warning 
        &amp; points would be deduced from result table basing on the range the 
        team&#8217;s disciplinary point fall into &amp; educate the players about 
        the importance of fair play .</p>
      <p><font color="#FF0000">22. Any player reaching 3 disciplinary points will 
        be given an automatic one match ban. A further automatic one match ban 
        will follow each time 3 disciplinary points are earned by that player. 
        </font></p>
      <p>23. Any Team or any player that earns significant disciplinary points 
        during the season would be the subject of specific disciplinary action 
        taken by the Committee.<br>
        <br>
      </p>
      <p><strong>Citation procedure</strong><br>
        <br>
        24. A Referee or a Team may file a Citation with the Committee concerning 
        incidences which occur during a game.</p>
      <p>25. A Citation may only be filed following serious incidences such as 
        violent or abusive behaviour.</p>
      <p>26. Each Citation must contain full details of the alleged incidences 
        and must end with a recommendation for disciplinary action.</p>
      <p>27. The Citation must be filed by the end of the Tuesday following the 
        game although a Citation filed late may be considered by the Committee.</p>
      <p>28. Following receipt of a Citation, the match Referee and the other 
        Team (as appropriate) will be sent the Citation and invited to submit 
        their views. Views must be submitted to the Committee within two days. 
      </p>
      <p>29 . The Chairman of the Committee will discuss the Citation(s) with 
        the Referees&#8217; representative on the Committee and the match Referee, 
        after which the Chairman will send the Citation(s) and the views received 
        to each member of the Committee together with a recommendation for disciplinary 
        action.</p>
      <p>30. The Committee will inform the relevant Team of its decision and notify 
        the rest of the rest of the Teams in the League.</p>
      <p>31. Disciplinary action may include (but will not be limited to) match 
        bans for individual players, points deducted for Teams and Teams being 
        thrown out of the League.<br>
